article.description: — Camren Hunter had 20 points in Central Arkansas' 72-67 victory against Arkansas State on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Central Arkansas beats Arkansas State 72-67
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- — Camren Hunter had 20 points in Central Arkansas' 72-67 victory against Arkansas State on Tuesday night. Hunter had seven rebounds and six assists for the Bears (5-4). Elias Cato scored 14 points while going 5 of 6 from the floor and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line, and added eight rebounds and three blocks. Collin Cooper recorded 13 points with three 3-pointers. The Red Wolves (5-4) were led in scoring by Caleb Fields, who finished with 16 points and seven assists. Omar El-Sheikh added 13 points and 10 rebounds for Arkansas State. Markise Davis also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
